          "body": "Mark structures the crucifixion narrative around Psalm 22. Verse 24 — *they divided up His garments... casting lots* — quotes Psalm 22:18 nearly verbatim. Verse 29 — *those passing by were hurling abuse at Him, wagging their heads* — echoes Psalm 22:7. Verse 31 — *He saved others; He cannot save Himself* — echoes Psalm 22:8 (*let Him deliver him, since He delights in him*). Verse 34 — *My God, My God, why have You forsaken Me?* — quotes Psalm 22:1 in Aramaic. Mark is not merely citing prophecy; he is showing that the entire crucifixion is the embodied performance of a Davidic lament that ends in resurrection vindication (Psalm 22:22-31). The cry of forsakenness presupposes the whole psalm — including its triumphant ending."
