          "body": "Mark 15:38-39 places two events side by side: the temple veil is torn (*schizō*) from top to bottom, and the centurion confesses Jesus as Son of God. Mark uses *schizō* only twice in his Gospel — at the baptism (1:10, the heavens *torn open*) and here. The Gospel opens and closes with a tearing — heaven torn down to enter Jesus, and the veil torn open to release access. The centurion's confession is the human counterpart: the barrier between Gentile and the Son of God is also torn. Mark's apocalyptic theology emerges in narrative form: the death of Jesus is the cosmic moment when every barrier — between God and man, between Jew and Gentile, between holy and common — is split apart."
