          "body": "After the crowd, priests, soldiers, and passers-by have spoken, the chapter ends with four named witnesses: Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James and Joses, Salome (15:40), and Joseph of Arimathea (15:43). The women *watched* (*theōreō*, 15:40, 47); Joseph *gathered up courage* (*tolmaō*, 15:43). The Twelve are absent — they have scattered (14:50). In the moral and physical wreckage of the cross, the gospel is preserved by a small group of women and one council member whose name will not appear again. Mark's pastoral message to a persecuted Roman church: when public discipleship fails, faithful witness survives in the unlikely few who stayed to watch."
